reinforcements sent to the gulf to augment the approximately 
230000 personnel then in the area fewer than 50000 reservists 
had been put on active duty most were in support roles to provide 
sealift and airlift of troops and supplies as well as medical 
service 
of the increases in authorized callups for the four services 
the biggest is for the army cheney raised its limit to 115000 
from 80000 but the largest proportional increase is for the navy 
whose limit triples from 10000 to 30000 up to now the navy has 
put 6182 reservists on active duty for desert shield 
the navy public affairs office said it could not immediately 
explain the reason for the large increase 
the limit for the marines was raised from 15000 to 23000 the 
air force ceiling remains at 20000 and there is no change in the 
coast guard limit of 1250 
