public gatherings were banned 
in april 1987 and january 1988 then lt col aldo rico led 
barracks revolts in a bid to halt the trials of officers accused of 
human rights abuses during the 197683 military dictatorship force 
generals to retire and the government to increase the military 
budget 
rico was imprisoned and cashiered but following the revolts 
most trials were halted military pay was increased and a number of 
generals retired 
the december 1988 insurrection led by col mohamed ali seineldin 
had similar motives and results 
he was forced to retire but army chief gen jose caridi and a 
number of other generals retired soldiers received pay increases 
and nearly 300 officers who faced trial eventually were pardoned by 
menem 
