two israeli soldiers were slightly wounded in the clash which 
occurred in the western sector near the village of ramayah 2 
miles north of the israeli settlement of zarit the army said 
israeli forces from the givati infantry brigade were on an 
initiated action when they spotted a squad of guerrillas heading 
toward the israeli border and they opened fire from a short 
distance an army statement said 
troops found a law antitank bazooka grenade launchers and 
magazines from a sovietdesigned kalashnikov rifle near the body of 
the slain guerrilla the army said 
it was not immediately known to which organization the 
guerrillas belonged 
in lebanon the moslemrun voice of the nation said the israelis 
brought tanks to reinforce their troops and helicopter gunships 
strafed suspected guerrilla positions in the region after daybreak 
todays clash followed a spate of incidents involving israeli 
soldiers or their militia allies in or around the 
israelicontrolled zone in south lebanon 
on monday israelibacked lebanese militiamen killed five 
guerrillas who according to an army statement belonged to a 
lebanese branch of the baath party and the lebanese resistance 
front 
last week five israeli soldiers from the givati brigade and two 
palestinian guerrillas were killed in a clash on the eastern sector 
of the buffer zone the army said those guerrillas belonged to the 
popular front for the liberation of palestine a plo faction led by 
george habash 
israel carved out the 440squaremile buffer zone to protect its 
northern border against guerrilla raids in 1985 when it withdrew 
the bulk of its forces from lebanon after a threeyear occupation 
the zone is jointly patrolled by israeli soldiers and some 2700 
members of the mostly christian south lebanon army militia 
