a brass band played santa claus handed 
out candy to tots and balloons filled the air today as two 
charlestonbased ships returned from a sixmonth deployment in the 
persian gulf 
the guided missile frigates uss taylor and robert g bradley 
were in the gulf when iraq invaded kuwait last aug 2 
since then the vessels were involved in intercepting more than 
500 ships and boats in the gulf boats were stopped or questioned 
to enforce the united nations blockade against iraq 
in august the bradley fired across the bow of an iraqi tanker 
the taylor did not discharge its guns during its sixmonth tour 
said cmdr kevin green of summerville sc 
we went over there without any expectation this type of thing 
would happen green said we were prepared for it of course 
all of us have the feeling that when the show is going down 
you want to be a part of it but when the show was going down in 
august we were a part of it for four months in the gulf we were 
very busy he said 
