system general electric is under contract to develop three of the 
systems 
the report said testimony at committee hearings revealed that 
more than 800 people will be needed to develop the software 
programs for the seawolf and integrate an estimated 32 million 
lines of code the contractor the report said was having trouble 
finding qualified workers for the task 
the navy has a dismal track record on combat computer system 
acquisition the report said it said the policy was based on a 
buy now fix later philosophy under which the navy purchases 
components before all the problems are worked out 
the navy is developing bsy2 separately from the rest of the 
seawolf on the premise that the combat system will be ready for 
installation when the rest of the submarine is completed said 
