patino were convicted of murder or manslaughter 
in allowing the jury to deliberate the charges and deliver a 
finding owens preserved the prosecutors right to appeal any 
verdict he dismissed 
but owens tossed out several charges before the case went to the 
jury citing a lack of evidence those counts included one of two 
murder charges against serrano a gun possession charge against 
patino and assault for both men 
the main prosecution witnesses were gina feliciano and her 
mother phyllis dagata the two women said they watched from their 
secondfloor window as the mob pursued the blacks around a corner 
where the shooting took place 
but they were unable to place serrano or patino at the scene and 
their testimony was filled with inconsistencies and contradictions 
fama is serving 32 and twothirds years to life for his 
conviction keith mondello the ringleader was acquitted of murder 
and manslaughter but convicted of several lesser crimes he was 
sentenced to five and onethird years to 16 years 
several other defendants are scheduled to stand trial early next 
year including charles stressler whose first case ended in a 
mistrial 
