<DOCNO> AP901204-0168 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
scientists on tuesday displayed the 
first picture taken by what will soon be the worlds most powerful 
optical telescope a huge instrument designed to peer deeper into 
space than ever before 
when it is completed the 942 million keck telescope at mauna 
kea hawaii will be the worlds largest with a mirror 10 meters 
in diameter it also is the first to be built of automated mirror 
segments 
astronomers say the keck will enable them to gaze back 12 
billion years in time by revealing light images still traveling 
toward earth 
these are really time machines given the finite speed of 
light said edward stone chairman of the california association 
of research in astronomy composed of scientists from the 
california institute of technology and the university of 
california 
the photo of galaxy ngc 1232 taken with only a quarter of the 
kecks 36 mirror segments in place more than matched the quality 
of images from the worlds largest effective telescope the 5meter 
hale telescope at palomar observatory 
the image was taken nov 24 from the wm keck observatory on 
mauna kea a 13796foot volcano on the island of hawaii 
the picture of the galaxy 65 million light years from earth in 
the constellation eridanus marks the telescopes first light 
a term astronomers use to describe the first viewing through a new 
telescope 
the photo has no particular scientific value ngc 1232 was 
selected simply to demonstrate the optical quality of the 
telescope said mirror designer jerry nelson an astronomer at the 
university of california berkeley 
when we first saw the picture we were really thrilled said 
nelson we were all hopping up and down 
the telescope wont be fully functioning until late next year 
with all mirror segments in place and precision cameras mounted to 
record the images it returns 
when it is completed the keck telescope is expected to be twice 
as powerful as the hale and far more accurate and reliable than a 
6meter soviet telescope that is frequently inoperable 
the keck differs from other large telescopes in that its mirror 
is made up of separate hexagonal mirror segments 6 feet in 
diameter the aluminumcoated mirrors are kept in alignment within 
1millionth of an inch by computercontrolled sensors 
stone said a singlepiece 10meterwide mirror probably could 
not be constructed with existing technology 
the telescope will offer research opportunities not possible 
with the hubble space telescope launched earlier this year by a 
space shuttle because it orbits earth above the distorting effects 
of the atmosphere the 15 billion hubble space telescope was 
supposed to see farther into the universe than the keck even 
though the hubble has a smaller mirror 
nasa discovered after it was launched that the hubbles mirror 
was flawed during construction rendering it less powerful than 
planned until a space shuttle crew can fix it in 1993 
however the keck with its large lightgathering mirror will 
be a better instrument for analyzing the light spectrums of stars 
stone said this will enable scientists to better understand the 
nature of the stars and calculate their speed 
by providing images that reach back 12 billion years scientists 
will see stars as they appeared some 3 billion years after the 
birth of the universe palomar by contrast reaches back only 8 
billion years 
caltech and the university of california are sharing the cost of 
the telescope caltech aided by a 70 million grant from the wm 
keck foundation put up the 87 million the project originally was 
expected to cost overruns of 72 million will be shared by the 
two universities and uc will pay the annual operating cost of 
about 3 million stone said 
nelson said mauna kea is considered the worlds best site for a 
telescope because its high altitude reduces atmospheric 
distortions but the thin air often impairs researchers thinking 
ability and causes severe headaches he said as a result 
operations must be carefully planned and monitored by the projects 
sealevel headquarters 
</TEXT>
