stereo vcr this one piece of hardware should be as central to 
your home video system as the tv tube itself its much more 
versatile and its the easiest purchase to justify 
a stereo vcr converts any television into a stereo tv by 
delivering its right and left audio channels to your home audio 
system its the biggest cheapest single improvement you can make 
to a conventional tv 
with the stereo vcr hooked up and tuned in and your good old 
19inch blackandwhite philco between the speakers you have 
stereo tv 
it gives you much finer acoustic detail to go along with the 
video image and youll be surprised at how much a good soundtrack 
enhances your viewing 
and theres a lot to hear most major tv markets have more than 
one stereo broadcaster most cable systems can deliver a stereo 
signal and most videocassettes sold and rented today are in 
stereo 
with that much programming available its just foolish not to 
upgrade 
when youre shopping remember a twohead or fourhead 
or hifi vcr isnt necessarily a stereo model every vcr needs 
one tape head to play and one head to record fourhead models 
allow for slowmotion freeze frames and other special effects 
with a stereo vcr you also get sap or secondary audio program 
services also known as mts or multichannel television sound pbs 
stations use it for descriptive narrative weather reports and 
simultaneous translation to a second language 
fullfeatured models retail for 300 to 450 but basic models 
can be had for less than 250 
