ivory the bostonians room with a view is richly 
talented in evoking the spirit and the look of a bygone time and 
place he has directed an expert cast particularly blythe danner 
as indias freethinking best friend and simon callow as a waspish 
psychiatrist the bridges children are well played by robert sean 
leonard margaret welsh and kyra sedgwick 
the miramax films release is rated pg13 for adult situations 
running time 124 minutes 
by bob thomas associated press writer 
 
havana 
 
havana 1958 a time and place when rum flowed as freely as fast 
bucks at the craps table and sex was as open as a 50foot ketch 
americans came in wild abandon to soak up the withering spoils of 
corrupt cuban dictator fulgencio batista 
it was the twilight of the aristocracy and the dawn of the 
peasant when the rumba met the revolutionary and more than just 
the music died 
sydney pollack shakes the death rattle in havana his 
bittersweet love story of a highrolling gambler named jack played 
by robert redford who comes to havana for the biggest poker game 
of his career and instead falls in love with roberta duran lena 
olin a swedish revolutionary 
roberta is married to an influential aristocrat raul julia who 
supports fidel castro and the rebel forces 
redford looking like he just stepped off the set of the way 
we were in his allamerican 50s garb arrives in havana on the 
car ferry just as batistas thugs board the boat in search of 
contraband translation weapons for the rebel forces roberta 
looks mighty sweaty through it all and an effete food writer 
daniel davis who we immediately know works for the company 
translation cia looks on with grand bemusement and interest 
robertas car carries a cache of americanissue military weapons 
and ammunition she hires jack to drive the car through customs 
because she fears batistas men already have her fingered they 
probably noticed the look of pure terror on her face 
jack a middleaged guy whos gone through life committed to 
nothing but his one pleasures and nomad existence is fascinated by 
roberta a sensual deeply committed woman committed to her 
marriage and husband and to the cause shes everything he isnt 
jack is also drawn towards arturo robertas husband who 
mesmerizes with his eyes his genteel ways but the revolution is 
meaningless for jack who merely follows the game wherever it might 
be 
but these are dangerous times with dangerous players the durans 
are arrested arturo is believed dead roberta is taken off to be 
tortured 
</TEXT>
