<TEXT>
jacks loyalties to gambling and to his emotions collide he 
carries his desire to save roberta to the big game with its 
selective group of heavy hitters including the head of batistas 
security police jack does a nono he mixes politics with cards 
but through his wits he manages to free roberta he hides her 
in his rooms but she doesnt stay the revolution cant wait 
cuba is falling apart as the new year approaches batista is 
about to flee and castro is about to come down from the hills 
roberta puts her life on the line and the rebels regard her as a 
leader jack puts his life on the line to find her and spirit her 
to safety in miami and especially by falling in love with her 
it is the eve of success for the revolution and heres where 
the screenplay falls completely apart a woman of such intense 
commitment to such an intense cause would hardly abandon it and the 
people who depend on her for a man especially one like jack 
but a predictable twist shakes her back to her destiny 
pollack avoids the polemics of the rebel cause and aims his 
camera on the decadence and brutality of the batista regime hes 
in his hemingway mode the colors the booze the women the 
fearlessness the intrigue the flirtation with death and dying 
but the movie lacks any real hard edge or toughness 
the movie ends years later theres a voiceover as jack gazes 
out to sea in key west fla watching the sunset and the ships 
afterall roberta might be on one another hemingway nudge 
pollack is a thoughtful and intelligent director who is very 
good with character development he wins with roberta the jurys 
still out with jack 
unfortunately theres very little sensuality between the two 
stars redford is far too restrained and distant to add fuel to 
olins natural fire she is an extremely talented and passionate 
actress who scorched the screen in enemies a love story and 
the unbearable lightness of being another love story set 
against the politics confusion and death of a revolution 
redford is likewise a cold fish in whats supposed to be one of 
the films hot scenes and an example of the fast life in havana a 
menage a trois with a two american tourists 
there are touches of grim wit in havana provided by alan 
arkin as the casino boss and second in command to mobster meyer 
