<TEXT>
the testing of globex an electronic global 
trading system developed by chicagos futures exchanges will get 
underway at the end of the first quarter of next year a spokesman 
for one of the exchanges said tuesday 
globex is being developed by the chicago mercantile exchange 
the chicago board of trade and reuters holdings plc it will link 
investors in north america europe and asia through an electronic 
system for trading futures and options contracts 
it will operate during hours when the mercantile exchange and 
board of trade trading floors are closed 
andrew yemma a spokesman for the mercantile exchange said the 
testing of globex will involve about 250 terminals stationed in 
chicago new york and london 
the goal of the testing is to make sure the system performs 
totally up to its capabilities before it is placed into service 
yemma said 
the results of the testing will determine the actual launch date 
for globex 
yemma said negotiations are continuing between the exchanges and 
reuters for a final agreement on operating the system when an 
agreement is finalized it will be submitted to the exchanges 
membership for approval 
globex was the idea of the mercantile exchange after initial 
opposition the board of trade decided earlier this year to join 
the merc in developing the system abandoning plans to develop its 
own 24hour electronic trading system 
reuters a british news agency and disseminator of financial 
news and market information is providing the technical expertise 
</TEXT>
