york 
the dollar first slumped after the fed said it was relaxing its 
reserve requirements for banks an unusual move aimed at 
stimulating the deteriorating economy by easing a shortage of 
credit 
the central bank said its action the first change in reserve 
requirements since 1983 was taken in part for technical reasons 
but also to encourage banks to increase lending 
ideally if banks have more money to lend interest rates would 
fall although some private economists questioned whether that 
would in fact be the result of the fed move but the foreign 
exchange markets taking no chances sold the dollar down 
the dollar like all currencies draws support from higher 
interest rates which make us investments more attractive when 
rates fall the dollar tends to follow suit 
the us currency took another hit shortly before the close of 
trading after a british news report said iraq may be ready to 
withdraw from most of kuwait as long as it is allowed to keep the 
disputed rumailah oil field 
the report raised the prospects for a peaceful end to the middle 
east crisis the dollar seen as a relatively safe investment in 
times of international strife has advanced as tensions increased 
in recent months and dropped as they were defused 
james t mcgroarty senior vice president with greenwich capital 
markets inc noted that the dollar stormed higher last week as the 
persian gulf situation appeared to worsen that surge upward made 
the dollar particularly vulnerable to a sharp decline he said 
the british pound rose against the dollar tuesday in new york 
sterling closed at 192925 up from 19180 late monday in london 
earlier the pound rose to 19255 from 19205 late monday 
the dollar fell to 13330 japanese yen in new york from 134735 
late monday in tokyo overnight the dollar rose 135 yen to a 
closing 13435 yen and it was later quoted in london at 13400 
yen 
other late dollar rates in new york compared with mondays late 
quotes included 15030 german marks down from 151395 12825 
swiss francs down from 12935 50825 french francs down from 
51135 112925 italian lire down from 113800 and 116325 
canadian dollars down from 116625 
