<TEXT>
sutton holding corp a new york investment 
group that has been pursuing desoto inc proposed acquiring the 
manufacturer through a merger 
in a letter to des plaines illbased desotos board of 
directors sutton chairman william spier proposed a merger in which 
stockholders would get 425 per share in cash and securities 
the securities would entitle shareholders to a pro rata share in 
the proceeds from any dissolution of desotos pension plans 
this security could be distributed as a dividend to desoto 
stockholders immediately prior to consummation of our 
acquisition spier said in the letter dated dec 3 which was 
included in a sutton filing with the securities and exchange 
commission 
in october desoto shareholders approved a plan to sell off most 
of the companys assets and terminate its pension plans in return 
for a onetime dividend of 3550 per share 
under the restructuring the company would sell substantially all 
of its businesses including its domestic consumer paint business 
which has supplied sears roebuck amp co for 80 years 
only desotos detergent business would be retained 
desoto has estimated that the partial liquidation and 
restructuring would raise about 222 million before taxes with 85 
million earmarked to retire corporate debt 
it noted that its plan to terminate pension plans and recover 
some 28 million in excess assets is subject to approval by the 
internal revenue service and the pension benefit guaranty corp 
the federal agency that guarantees workers pensions much like the 
federal deposit insurance corp guarantees bank deposits 
