<TEXT>
northwest airlines is planning on retaining 
its ranking as the nations fourth largest carrier despite a spate 
of setbacks the carrier has suffered in recent years 
the public knows we run a safe airline and an airline of 
integrity these things can happen to any airline northwest 
spokesman doug miller said after the latest disaster a runway 
collision monday that left eight people dead at detroit 
metropolitan airport 
in the past four years northwest has suffered through two 
crashes a takeover bitter labor strife and the convictions of 
three pilots for flying while intoxicated 
mondays runway collision came three years after northwest 
flight 255 went down near the same airport killing 156 people in 
the secondworst air crash in us history 
in that aug 16 1987 accident the md80 failed to gain 
altitude during takeoff and slammed into a highway overpass the 
national transportation safety board ruled that the pilots didnt 
set the planes wing flaps and slats properly for takeoff and that 
failure ff a cockpit warning device contributed to the crash 
northwest gained its fourthplace ranking behind united 
airlines american airlines and delta airlines after the 
eaganbased carrier acquired instate rival republic airlines for 
884 million in august 1986 
what followed was an epidemic of late flights and lost baggage 
roundly attributed to union warfare that stemmed from pay 
disparities as union leaders fought the company for more than two 
years to unify contracts many former republic workers were getting 
paid less than their northwest counterparts 
by the time los angeles investor al checchi led a 365 billion 
buyout completed aug 3 1989 the airline was fighting to overcome 
a new nickname northworst 
checchi ushered in new management and improved service the 
airline in march 1988 already had scored points with some travelers 
by banning smoking on all of its domestic flights not just on 
flights of two hours or less as federal rules mandated 
but other problems mounted 
on dec 28 1989 northwest publicized a bomb threat it received 
for a dec 30 flight from paris to detroit more than 100 people 
canceled their reservations for the flight 28 passengers and 14 
crew members made the trip 
on jan 4 1990 an engine fell off a threeengine northwest 
plane flying from miami to minneapolis the boeing 727 landed 
safely in tampa fla federal officials said improper maintenance 
was involved and proposed a 200000 fine 
then on march 8 1990 three northwest pilots flying a boeing 
727 from fargo nd were arrested at minneapolisst paul 
international airport after authorities were alerted that the 
pilots had been drinking heavily the night before the three became 
the first commercial pilots to be convicted for flying a jetliner 
while intoxicated their sentences ranged from one year to 16 
months 
that was followed with a company report in october that ground 
workers in atlanta filled the hydraulic systems of two dc9 jets 
with a mixture of hand soap and hydraulic fluid the airline said 
it was a mistake fifty flights were canceled around the country 
and 12 dc9s were grounded for inspections 
checchi called a news conference oct 16 to say that layoffs and 
a reduced flight schedule were imminent because of higher jet fuel 
prices brought on by iraqs aug 2 invasion of kuwait 
but at the same meeting he told reporters the airline was in 
good financial shape and positioned to possibly acquire another 
airline or part of another airline the takeover debt stands at 
17 billion two years ahead of schedule and the company has cash 
reserves of 1 billion available 
despite a 47 percent drop in its thirdquarter earnings 
northwests market share in the first 10 months of this year was 
117 percent up 07 percent from the same period a year ago 
although northwest and other us carriers are expected to lose 
a total of more than 1 billion in the fourth quarter checchi said 
last week in an interview with the star tribune that he was content 
with the airlines position 
i feel that under circumstances were in pretty good shape 
he said but its nothing to crow about 
